                PII <span>GALLERY</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="section-text">
                Philadelphia International Institute, better known as PII. Is an Eastern European and American
                Contemporary Gallery that displays predominantly Modern Art. It is located in the quiet neighborhood of
                Old City in Philadelphia, PA. The gallery is operated and owned by Margaret Berczynski. The gallery
                brings a much-needed array of international work including textile, printmaking, painting, sculpture and
                photography. With my approach towards this design, I focused on not stealing the individuality that the
                gallery processes while maintaining a respectable and progressive image. With the combination of
                pictorial and typographic logo design I achieved a logo that is approachable yet brings a certain level
                of prestige to the gallery as a whole. I decided to use the color palette as a further representation of
                the galleryâ€™s personality and dynamicity.
            </p>
